  .louder
    WHAT ARE GOLDSPRINTS?
  %hr
  %p
    Events where people race each other on bicycles fixed to rollers. More details can be found at 
    %a{:href => "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Goldsprint" } wikipedia.
   
  .louder
    WHAT IS THE OPENSPRINTS SOLUTION?
  %hr
  %p
    We 
    %a{:href=>"http://store.opensprints.org"} sell
    a digital timing system and offer an interactive racing 
    %a{:href=>"http://opensprints.org/downloads.html"} software application. 
    In order to conduct your very own Goldsprints race, you will need to source the following additional items:
    %ul
      %li Computer
      %li Projector + screen or TV (this depends on the video outputs on your computer)
      %li
        1 to 4 Rollers with forkstands (recommended). See the
        %a{:href=>"http://wiki.opensprints.org/index.php?title=Rollers"} wiki page
        on rollers for more information
      %li 1 to 4 Bikes

  .louder
    WHY IS THE PROJECT CALLED "OPENSPRINTS"?
  %hr
  %p
    The entire development source for the OpenSprints roller racing solution is free and accessible to all. A goal of the project is to promote learning, freedom, and community.
  %p
    We believe in the ideals touted by such organizations as the 
    %a{:href => "http://fsf.org"} Free Software Foundation
    and
    %a{:href => "http://blog.makezine.com/archive/2006/12/the_makers_bill_of_rights.html"} The Maker's Bill of Rights.
    The development source for the OpenSprints solution is available to anyone to study, to modify for custom use, or to contribute enhancements and fixes. Go
    %a{:href => "http://github.com/evanfarrar/opensprints"} here
    for access to the source.
